--- RED cause analysis (acceptance-first first run, before fixes) ---
TEST-011.5/.6/.7: plugins/sdd-implementation/scripts/select-agent-model.sh is
committed without the executable bit (mode 100644; the repo's own test.yml
comment already documents this class of issue: "Windows-authored commits
record mode 100644"). Fix: invoke it via `bash "$SELECT_MODEL_SH" ...`
instead of relying on the committed exec bit, matching the exact convention
already used for the bash suite-registration steps in .github/workflows/test.yml.
TEST-013.2: the restricted PATH fixture was too aggressive -- it omitted
`dirname`, which select-agent-model.sh's own top-level registry-path default
(`dirname "$0"`) needs unconditionally, before it ever reaches its
python3-availability check. Fix: add a `dirname` symlink to the restricted
PATH directory so the script can reach its own runtime check.
